  "prompt": "Why did Johnny Cash spend time in prison?",
  "response": "Johnny Cash never actually spent time in prison in the traditional sense; however, he did have several encounters with the law throughout his life. Most notably, he was arrested multiple times for offenses related to alcohol, including public intoxication. One of the more famous incidents occurred in 1965 when he was arrested in El Paso, Texas, for possession of amphetamines and was briefly jailed. \n\nAdditionally, Cash often performed at prisons, most famously at Folsom State Prison in 1968, which gave him a deep connection to those incarcerated and inspired his music. His experiences and empathy for the incarcerated became prominent themes in his work, as he frequently addressed issues of justice and redemption in his songs. Cash's connection to prison culture through his music and performances has often led to confusion about his personal experiences with incarceration.",
